56 void BaseConstraint::function(const Eigen::Ref<const Eigen::VectorXd>& x, Eigen::Ref<Eigen::VectorXd> out) const
57 {
58  auto current_values = calcError(x);
59  for (std::size_t i{ 0 }; i < bounds_.size(); ++i)
60  {
61  out[i] = bounds_[i].distance(current_values[i]);
62  }
63 }

65 void BaseConstraint::jacobian(const Eigen::Ref<const Eigen::VectorXd>& x, Eigen::Ref<Eigen::MatrixXd> out) const
66 {
67  auto current_values = calcError(x);
68  auto current_jacobian = calcErrorJacobian(x);
69 
70  for (std::size_t i{ 0 }; i < bounds_.size(); ++i)
71  {
72  if (current_values[i] > bounds_[i].upper + getTolerance())
73  {
74  out.row(i) = current_jacobian.row(i);
75  }
76  else if (current_values[i] < bounds_[i].lower - getTolerance())
77  {
78  out.row(i) = -current_jacobian.row(i);
79  }
80  else
81  {
82  out.row(i) = Eigen::VectorXd::Zero(n_);
83  }
84  }
85 }

91 void PositionConstraint::parseConstraintMsg(moveit_msgs::Constraints constraints)
92 {
93  bounds_.clear();
94  bounds_ = positionConstraintMsgToBoundVector(constraints.position_constraints.at(0));
95  ROS_INFO_STREAM("Parsed x constraints" << bounds_[0]);
96  ROS_INFO_STREAM("Parsed y constraints" << bounds_[1]);
97  ROS_INFO_STREAM("Parsed z constraints" << bounds_[2]);
98 
99  // extract target / nominal value
100  geometry_msgs::Point position =
101  constraints.position_constraints.at(0).constraint_region.primitive_poses.at(0).position;
102  target_ << position.x, position.y, position.z;
103 
104  // target_pose_ should replace target
105  Eigen::Quaterniond temp_quat;
106  tf::quaternionMsgToEigen(constraints.position_constraints[0].constraint_region.primitive_poses[0].orientation,
107  temp_quat);
108  target_pose_ = Eigen::Translation3d(position.x, position.y, position.z) * temp_quat;
109 }

112 {
113  return target_pose_.rotation().transpose() * (forwardKinematics(x).translation() - target_pose_.translation());

124 void AngleAxisConstraint::parseConstraintMsg(moveit_msgs::Constraints constraints)
125 {
126  bounds_.clear();
127  bounds_ = orientationConstraintMsgToBoundVector(constraints.orientation_constraints.at(0));
128  ROS_INFO_STREAM("Parsing angle-axis constraints");
129  ROS_INFO_STREAM("Parsed rx / roll constraints" << bounds_[0]);
130  ROS_INFO_STREAM("Parsed ry / pitch constraints" << bounds_[1]);
131  ROS_INFO_STREAM("Parsed rz / yaw constraints" << bounds_[2]);
132 
133  // extract target / nominal value
134  // for orientation we can save the target in different formats, probably quaternion is the best one here
135  // we could use a 3 vector to be uniform with position constraints, but this makes us vulnerable to
136  // singularities, wich could occur here as the target can be an arbitrary orientation
137  tf::quaternionMsgToEigen(constraints.orientation_constraints.at(0).orientation, target_as_quat_);
138 
139  // so we could do this:
140  // target_ = target_as_quat_.toRotationMatrix().eulerAngles(0, 1, 2);
141  // but calcCurrentValues and calcCurrentJacobian use target_as_quat_
142 }

144 Eigen::VectorXd AngleAxisConstraint::calcError(const Eigen::Ref<const Eigen::VectorXd>& x) const
145 {
146  // I'm not sure yet whether I want the error expressed in the current ee_frame, or target_frame,
147  // or world frame. This implementation expressed the error in the end-effector frame.
148  Eigen::Matrix3d Rerror = forwardKinematics(x).rotation().transpose() * target_as_quat_;
149  Eigen::AngleAxisd aa(Rerror);
150  double angle = aa.angle();
151  assert(std::abs(angle) < M_PI);
152  return aa.axis() * angle;
153 }

155 // mysterious minus sign in Jacobian, found through trial and error...
156 Eigen::MatrixXd AngleAxisConstraint::calcErrorJacobian(const Eigen::Ref<const Eigen::VectorXd>& x) const
157 {
158  // Eigen::AngleAxisd aa {forwardKinematics(x).rotation().transpose() * target_as_quat_};
159 
160  Eigen::AngleAxisd aa{ forwardKinematics(x).rotation() };
161  return -angularVelocityToAngleAxis(aa.angle(), aa.axis()) * geometricJacobian(x).bottomRows(3);
162 }

186 Eigen::VectorXd RPYConstraints::calcError(const Eigen::Ref<const Eigen::VectorXd>& x) const
187 {
188  // I'm not sure yet whether I want the error expressed in the current ee_frame, or target_frame,
189  // or world frame. This implementation expressed the error in the end-effector frame.
190  Eigen::Matrix3d error = forwardKinematics(x).rotation().transpose() * target_as_quat_;
191  return error.eulerAngles(0, 1, 2);
192 
193  // alternative, calculate difference of euler angles and try to live with singularities
194  // Eigen::Vector3d error = forwardKinematics(x).rotation().eulerAngles(0, 1, 2) - target_;
195  // return error;
196 }

198 Eigen::MatrixXd RPYConstraints::calcErrorJacobian(const Eigen::Ref<const Eigen::VectorXd>& x) const
199 {
200  // use the euler angles of the current end-effector orientation expressed in the world frame
201  // we need this to convert the geometric jacobian to an analytical one that can be used for rpy angles
202  // the jacobian is expressed in the world frame, so should the rpy angles I suppose...
203  auto rpy = forwardKinematics(x).rotation().eulerAngles(0, 1, 2);
204  return angularVelocityToRPYRates(rpy[0], rpy[1]) * geometricJacobian(x).bottomRows(3);
205 }

208  * Position and orienation constraints
209  * Using angle axis error for orientation
210  * ****************************************/
211 void PoseConstraints::parseConstraintMsg(moveit_msgs::Constraints constraints)
212 {
213  bounds_.clear();
214  bounds_ = positionConstraintMsgToBoundVector(constraints.position_constraints.at(0));
215  ROS_INFO_STREAM("Parsed x constraints" << bounds_[0]);
216  ROS_INFO_STREAM("Parsed y constraints" << bounds_[1]);
217  ROS_INFO_STREAM("Parsed z constraints" << bounds_[2]);
218 
219  // extract target / nominal value
220  geometry_msgs::Point position =
221  constraints.position_constraints.at(0).constraint_region.primitive_poses.at(0).position;
222  target_ << position.x, position.y, position.z;
223 
224  auto ori_bounds = orientationConstraintMsgToBoundVector(constraints.orientation_constraints.at(0));
225  bounds_.push_back(ori_bounds[0]);
226  bounds_.push_back(ori_bounds[1]);
227  // IGNORE RZ CONSTRAINT
228  tf::quaternionMsgToEigen(constraints.orientation_constraints.at(0).orientation, target_as_quat_);
229  ROS_INFO_STREAM("Parsed rx / roll constraints" << bounds_[3]);
230  ROS_INFO_STREAM("Parsed ry / pitch constraints" << bounds_[4]);
231  // ROS_INFO_STREAM("Parsed rz / yaw constraints" << bounds_[5]);
232 }

234 Eigen::VectorXd PoseConstraints::calcError(const Eigen::Ref<const Eigen::VectorXd>& x) const
235 {
236  Eigen::Matrix<double, 5, 1> error;
237  auto fk_pose = forwardKinematics(x);
238  error.topRows(3) = fk_pose.translation() - target_;
239 
240  Eigen::Matrix3d Rerror = fk_pose.rotation().transpose() * target_as_quat_;
241  Eigen::AngleAxisd aa(Rerror);
242  double angle = aa.angle();
243  assert(std::abs(angle) < M_PI);
244  // error.bottomRows(3) = aa.axis() * angle;
245  error[3] = aa.axis()[0] * angle;
246  error[4] = aa.axis()[1] * angle;
247 
248  return error;
249 }

255 std::shared_ptr<BaseConstraint> createConstraint(robot_model::RobotModelConstPtr robot_model, const std::string& group,
256  moveit_msgs::Constraints constraints)
257 {
258  std::size_t num_dofs = robot_model->getJointModelGroup(group)->getVariableCount();
259  std::size_t num_pos_con = constraints.position_constraints.size();
260  std::size_t num_ori_con = constraints.orientation_constraints.size();
261 
262  if (num_pos_con > 0 && num_ori_con > 0)
263  {
264  ROS_ERROR_STREAM("Combining position and orientation constraints results in ignoring the z orientation tolerance value.");
265  auto pose_con = std::make_shared<PoseConstraints>(robot_model, group, num_dofs);
266  pose_con->init(constraints);
267  return pose_con;
268  }
269  else if (num_pos_con > 0)
270  {
271  if (num_pos_con > 1)
272  {
273  ROS_ERROR_STREAM("Only a single position constraints supported. Using the first one.");
274  }
275  auto pos_con = std::make_shared<PositionConstraint>(robot_model, group, num_dofs);
276  pos_con->init(constraints);
277  return pos_con;
278  }
279  else if (num_ori_con > 0)
280  {
281  if (num_ori_con > 1)
282  {
283  ROS_ERROR_STREAM("Only a single orientation constraints supported. Using the first one.");
284  }
285 
286  if (constraints.name == OrientationErrorType::ANGLE_AXIS)
287  {
288  ROS_INFO_STREAM("Creating orientation constraints of type: " << constraints.name);
289  auto ori_con = std::make_shared<AngleAxisConstraint>(robot_model, group, num_dofs);
290  ori_con->init(constraints);
291  return ori_con;
292  }
293  else if (constraints.name == OrientationErrorType::ROLL_PITCH_YAW)
294  {
295  ROS_INFO_STREAM("Creating orientation constraints of type: " << constraints.name);
296  auto ori_con = std::make_shared<RPYConstraints>(robot_model, group, num_dofs);
297  ori_con->init(constraints);
298  return ori_con;
299  }
300  else
301  {
302  ROS_ERROR_STREAM("Unkown type of orientation constraint: " << constraints.name);
303  return nullptr;
304  }
305  // auto ori_con = std::make_shared<RPYConstraints>(robot_model, group, constraints, num_dofs);
306  // auto ori_con = std::make_shared<QuaternionConstraint>(robot_model, group, constraints, num_dofs);
307  // ori_con->init(constraints);
308  }
309  else
310  {
311  ROS_ERROR_STREAM("No constraints found in planning request.");
312  return nullptr;
313  }
314 }
